name: Alexander J. Harb
text:
Usually this facility hums right along with activity and trucks are unloaded in under an hour but today the management has decided NOT to get some day labor forklift drivers here to help out with the extra volume of incoming freight.

Instead we are being detained up to 3 hours to get unloaded as the forklift drivers are given double duty inside the warehouse.

Usually this is a GREAT place to come and get unloaded quickly.

Not today....

name: Noe Salgado
text: Very poor Customer service, employees doing whatever they want to. Managers no where to find them. Deliveries not following schedules. Reps no placing the orders, I missed my orders 2 times last week and the week before. If you are trying to go out of business, you are doing a great job. I am wondering how many customers are in the same situation

name: Dave Vennell
text: Got here about an hour before appointment. Docks were full with an additional truck waiting. Was told to park next to guy waiting and to not block incoming vendor trucks. Took about 4 hours to get unloaded. Seemed like everyone was running around doing their own thing and there was no communication

name: Benjamin Barrett
text: Plenty of room to back Into docks friendly staff, but no overnight parking

name: David Ulmer
text: Easy to get in and back to docks.  Friendly people that unloaded me quickly.

name: Lindsey Brown
text: In/out under 1 hour. Very easy backing up to the dock.

name: Chuck Britt Jr
text: One word slooow! 5 hours to get unloaded. Another place I hope and pray 🙏 i never come back to!

name: kalyn montague
text:
Wheres that ten star button?
These guys are great and curtoues. Easy in and easy out.

name: Demetricus Travis
text: Fast in and out

name: susie stewart
text: Friendly staff, easy docks...2 hours to unload

name: Ed Mck
text: No over night parking. They can unload quick if they have to.

name: Jose Ramirez
text: Truckers be ready to kill all your hours of service when deliver to this place.... bad bad unloading process!!!!

name: al sanders
text: Warehouse manager sucks

name: Bryan Brown
text: Convenient spot. High prices, supposedly set by the Alabama ABC...

name: Nick Lowe
text: Great place. Friendly staff. Good selection.

name: brad fussman
text: Ask for prices rip off

resp.text: We appreciate you taking your time to leave feedback about our store. All hard liquor is controlled by Alabama Beverage Control Board - a division of the State of Alabama. The ABC Board controls alcoholic beverages through distribution, licensing, and enforcement. Essentially all liquor stores in Alabama have a middle man that we have to pay to operate and serve you. Thank you.

name: doug eckelkamp
text: I bought a case of bud light and 4 bags of ice from here. It was $47. I asked what the beer cost and was told that it was $30 plus tax. I asked why they were more than the grocery stores  They said that the grocery stores sell beer with less alcohol content. I checked on it with AB and was told that it was a lie. Don't buy alcohol from here. The bud light is $12 less a case at the grocery stores.  There liquor is twice as much as it should be.  They don't have prices on their products. it looks like they charge whatever they want.

name: Christy Chancey
text: If I could give zero stars, I would. We walked to this store at 8:30 p.m...all the lights were off, and the door was locked even though all of their signs and website says they're open untill 11pm. No one wants to answer the phone. Good job Seaside, way to keep it classy. Will spread the word and will never be back. Idiots

text: Walked there from my hotel for him to lock up and turn the OPEN sign off as I walked up to the door. Another fella was right behind me too but he wouldn’t let us in even though it was 4 minutes till closing time.
